=====Usage notes=====
* {{sense|language}} In English, the word ''know'' is often omitted. If asked whether he is able to communicate in Italian, for instance, an English native would respond ''I don't speak Italian''. This means that he does not know how to speak Italian, rather than that he does not want to speak Italian. If he does indeed not want to speak in Italian, he might reply ''I do not wish to speak in Italian'', or something similar. Most of the time, this is obvious by context anyway.

